c:["$","p",null,{"children":["$","em",null,{"children":["Configures the global ",["$","code",null,{"children":"forgeLogger"}]," based on CLI flags.  Call this once at the start of a command's ",["$","code",null,{"children":"run()"}]," handler to align consola's output level with the user's intent:  - ",["$","code",null,{"children":"quiet"}]," or ",["$","code",null,{"children":"json"}]," sets level to 0 (silent) so only LAFS output appears. - ",["$","code",null,{"children":"verbose"}]," sets level to 4 (debug) for maximum detail. - Default level is 3 (info) which covers info, warn, error, and success."]}]}]
